														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4865872">
									

<p>My concern is that this feels too narratively close to the mask still; like the effects are clearly based off that; but so is a lot of the character and conflict here too, even if the actual way this plays out is quite different. What I mean is that Michael is basically a straight rip of Jim Carrey's character, with like, the same 'wants to help but is chaotic' vibe as the mask has already and it feels&#8230;very derivative.</p>
<p>Beyond this, I don't actually have a good idea of how this works: you mention the big twist is that michael is actually real sad and that's not an awful idea but I don't really get how you're like, intending building up to it? And I'm really not convinced it's enough of a twist to carry this: it kinda feels like it'd be better being very upfront with it and then really exploring like, the dichotomy of michael wanting everyone to be happy and like trying to help and him just being super depressed and hating life.</p>
<p>I also don't really have a good idea of what the core plot beats you want to hit are: there's like, an obvious opening where you introduce his powers, and then&#8230;I have no idea? You refer to interviews and some logs but it feels like they're expository regarding his powers over like, actually telling a story and imo that will make them really boring to read.</p>

							</div>

								
					
