														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4865859">
									

<p>I guess my central concern with this is that you have a really interesting setting for the story but I'm not really sure what you're like&#8230;actually going to do with it? Like, I'm not hugely familiar with Anderson so I'll defer to Conwell in terms of how well it fits into that canon; but my concern here is just&#8230;how do you link the pieces up?</p>
<p>Like, the idea that for every Gyrfalcon, there's a cybernetic doppleganger hunting down the human user is fine but what are you doing with this? How does the Broken God stuff tie into this article? How do the initial pair of cyborgs tie in?</p>
<p>My concern is that it feels like the stuff about an assassin android attempting to hunt down a human with a robot arm is by far the most interesting part of this pitch and that nothing else really builds off that well. Maybe it'd be best writing it as a tale from the perspective of one of the two cyborgs where you can like, really explore their motivations and have cool action sequences as they nearly but don't quite get their target or w/e?</p>

							</div>

								
					
