<p>Seeking Greenlight: Yes<br />
Genre: Drama/Emotional<br />
Type: article, later used in tales<br />
Dr. Ethan Millan is a 26 years old researher, who was trying to invent time-travel. After a few testruns on his machine, the mechanism exploded, taking his maker into another reality. He crashlanded into an O5 meeting. After he was questioned, it was clear, that he was from another reality (interview oppotrunity), and because he saw the O5s, he was given amnestics. Surpriseingly, it didn't work. After few tests, it became clear, that he somehow has immunity to seemingly all anomalous effects. Hes knowledge and intelligence has proven to be valuable, and after he has failed to recreate the accident he was in (different physics), he has requested to work in the foundation. After a psychic evaluation, it was clear that he will not give up the identity of the O5 council. His request was accepted, but he was under a strict survillance. He was testing Safe class objets, specifically which had some memetic effects (as he was immune). Later, he died in a containment breach. His corpse immideatly disappeared, and his body reanimated 3 minutes later, in the same position and state as he arrived into this universe. The compromised meetingroom was obviously abadoned, but he was discovered by some patrolling facilityguard wandering around curiosly. At this time, his class was updated from safe to euclid (may need help because I don't know how to do this). They explained him what happened (leaving out the classified bits) and he was accepted back as a researcher. The meeting room was reassigned as his personal arriving chamber, after dicovering, that after his death, he always back to that point. A few Keter testing was made with him, many of which resulted in his death (he is only immune to anomalous effects, not physical like breaking your bones). Later keter testing was only allowed, if it was really necessary, and if he has agreed with it (as he really dies, when he dies). The time between death and reanimation is usually between 30 seconds and 5 days.</p>
<p>My intention with this character are that some scp objects can be further explored, as they couldn't be studied. I intend to create some drama in tales, as his memories also die with him (some love affair with his assigned researher assistant, because he needs someone to fill in the blanks after he dies). Obviously I will create a normal article with containment procedures, but I need to know if this idea is too much or not. I'm open to new ideas. This character was inspired by Doctor Who's captain Jack Harrkness, just to be clear. The whole idea is that he is stuck in the timeline.</p>

							</div>

								
					
